Building and Installing libdmtx-php
-----------------------------------------------------------------

*****************************************************************
*****************************************************************
** IMPORTANT: This package will not work with the accompanying **
**            version of libdmtx. It was written to work with  **
**            an older version and requires updating before it **
**            will compile or run.                             **
*****************************************************************
*****************************************************************

1. libdmtx Installation
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

You shoud have installed libdmtx and have the libdmtx.h file
under ../libdmtx (or change include in dmtx_write.h).


2. libdmtx-php Installation
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

  1 - Run phpize command

  2 - Run ./configure [--prefix install directory]; make install

  3 - Configure php.ini file with -> extension=dmtx.so

  4 - Test with dmtx.php :)


3. Dependencies
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

These packages are required to install and run libdmtx-php:

  PHP:     http://www.php.net

If you are using an RPM-based system then you can test for the
following packages:

  php
  php-cli
  php-common
  php-devel


4. Anything Else?
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Is something missing from these instructions?  If you spent hours
searching for a solution that you feel should be included in this
file then please send a message to the mailing list:

   libdmtx-open_discussion@lists.sourceforge.net
